EFF deputy president Floyd Shivambu is facing Parliament’s joint committee on ethics, after he assaulted of a journalist in March. Shivambu assaulted Netwerk24 journalist Adrian de Kock. Following that he apologised for engaging in a scuffle with the journalist. WATCH: EFF'S SHIVAMBU MOERS JOURNALIST! Shivambu said the scuffle was a result of circumstances which included taking of photographs and persistence "to speak to me whilst receiving documents from staff members in order to attend the Standing Committee on Finance (SCOF)". He says he was in a hurry to attend a committee meeting. Shivambu said at the time that he accepts that his impatience with the journalist was inappropriate. "The scuffle happened and was never an assault on the Journalist or media freedom. I regret the incident and believe it should have been handled differently. I take full responsibility and apologise for engaging in a scuffle with a person I discovered after the incident is a Journalist,” he said at the time. 